abstract: The campaign said the photo, displayed on a webpage touting the candidate’s anti-racism plan, was posted by a contractor who didn’t know where it was taken.
snippet: The campaign said the photo, displayed on a webpage touting the candidate’s anti-racism plan, was posted by a contractor who didn’t know where it was taken.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign, struggling to build support among black voters, removed from its website a photo of a Kenyan woman that was used earlier this year to illustrate his plan to dismantle racism in the United States.

abstract: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
snippet: Ahead of a possible Democratic run for president, the former mayor of New York City reversed himself before an important party constituency: black voters.
lead_paragraph: Ahead of a potential Democratic presidential run, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York on Sunday reversed his longstanding support of the aggressive “stop-and-frisk” policing strategy that he pursued for a decade and that led to the disproportionate stopping of black and Latino people across the city.

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg had a surprisingly robust lead in the latest Des Moines Register and CNN poll. Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders and Joseph R. Biden Jr. were in a statistical tie for second.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Pete Buttigieg continues to surge in Iowa, leapfrogging Senator Elizabeth Warren and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to hold a commanding lead among likely Democratic caucusgoers, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.

abstract: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
snippet: Here are five things happened on the presidential campaign trail this week, as impeachment hearings began in Washington.
lead_paragraph: There was more upheaval in the 2020 race this week, as one new Democratic candidate entered, another moved closer to doing so and a Republican dropped his primary challenge to President Trump. Here’s a look at the highlights.

abstract: “Coming to Howard for the first time was seeing the beauty of blackness,” one alumnus said.
snippet: “Coming to Howard for the first time was seeing the beauty of blackness,” one alumnus said.
lead_paragraph: “Have you ever seen anything like this?” Ashley Maltbia-Burgess, a 2010 graduate of Howard University, asked. She was standing with a group of fellow alums and her wife, Ashlee, looking out onto the crowded campus lawn. “I always told my wife, you have to come here to believe this, to feel this energy.”

abstract: They want to lead the Democratic Party’s moderate wing. But it will not be easy to displace Joseph R. Biden Jr., and then battle Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders.
snippet: They want to lead the Democratic Party’s moderate wing. But it will not be easy to displace Joseph R. Biden Jr., and then battle Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders.
lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker gave a pep talk to donors at a Manhattan barbecue restaurant on Wednesday evening, declaring that he was close to qualifying for the Democratic primary debate in December. But Mr. Booker acknowledged uncertain times ahead in the race, according to two people in attendance: Every time he turned around, Mr. Booker said, another candidate was ready to jump in.

headline_main: Is There Room for One More Candidate?

abstract: Republicans are weighing whether to draw out the proceeding, hindering the presidential campaigns of several Senate Democrats, or seek a quicker resolution.
snippet: Republicans are weighing whether to draw out the proceeding, hindering the presidential campaigns of several Senate Democrats, or seek a quicker resolution.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Republicans are conflicted about how quickly to move on an impeachment trial against President Trump, with some arguing for a speedy vote on the charges and others seeing an opportunity to drag out the historic proceedings and tie down some Democratic senators at a prime moment in their presidential campaigns.

abstract: Julián Castro and Kamala Harris are pitching themselves partially on being a ‘first,’ but neither is gaining traction.
snippet: Julián Castro and Kamala Harris are pitching themselves partially on being a ‘first,’ but neither is gaining traction.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Julián Castro’s fund-raising appeal last month was blunt. “Tragic mistake,” the subject line read, emphatically written in all capital letters. “Only Latino candidate could be cut from debate stage.”

abstract: A suspect was in custody after a shooting at a high school north of Los Angeles, the police said. They said the suspect was a student and he carried out the attack on his birthday.
snippet: A suspect was in custody after a shooting at a high school north of Los Angeles, the police said. They said the suspect was a student and he carried out the attack on his birthday.
lead_paragraph: A 16-year-old student pulled a handgun from his backpack at a high school in Santa Clarita, Calif., on Thursday morning and shot five students, killing two, the authorities said. The gunman was in grave condition after shooting himself in the head, they said.
